{"ANADEM":[{"def":"A garland or fillet; a chaplet or wreath.","pos":""}],"ANADIPLOSIS":[{"def":"A repetition of the last word or any prominent word in a sentence or clause, at the beginning of the next, with an adjunct idea; as, \"He retained his virtues amidst all his misfortunes -- misfortunes which no prudence could foresee or prevent.","pos":""}],"ANADROM":[{"def":"A fish that leaves the sea and ascends rivers.","pos":""}],"ANADROMOUS":[{"def":"Ascending rivers from the sea, at certain seasons, for breeding, as the salmon, shad, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"Tending upwards; -- said of terns in which the lowest secondary segments are on the upper side of the branch of the central stem.","pos":""}]}